From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: GloriousEggroll <gloriouseggroll@gmail.com>
Date: Wed, 8 Jul 2026 08:40:00 -0600
Subject: [PATCH] winepulse: treat DualSense hotplug as new devices

Do not reconnect old DualSense mono speaker or haptic streams after a
controller is unplugged. Once the backing Pulse/ALSA device is gone, the old
stream is invalid and must not be retargeted to a later controller.

Expose a fresh endpoint id for each transient DualSense audio hotplug event
while still resolving that id back to the real Pulse device name for stream
creation and property queries. Keep the visible controller speaker sink on its
stable Pulse name, since games such as Spider-Man Remastered discover and reuse
that endpoint directly for controller speaker effects.
